children.subject:
Leaving the students answer open, but 162 definitely doesn't use 105, and from a past question here, it doesn't seem like 151 requires any knowledge of 105. 152's only prereq according to HKN's course guide is 61c, soI don't think it uses 105 knowledge.

If you're interested though, you should definitely take it!

history.content: For robotics, you should really take EE 120 & C128- these are the main systems classes (if you haven't done so).  I'm not sure how much 152 will help (computer architecture).  151 will be useful for FPGA's, but again, to know how to make your robot behave how you want it to requires 120/128.   As for 105, it will not be necessary, unless you physically wish to build all the analog parts (which is imo is really cool, but I am a bit biased there :)).

I'm interested in robotics, but also want to take some classes in systems (162/152/151). How important is 105 for either?

Thanks in advance
